# Styling and Accessibility

- Use Tailwind CSS for styling patterns and consistency.
- Keep layouts responsive across laptop and desktop hackathon setups.
- Use semantic HTML for structure and assistive technologies.
- Add `aria-label` attributes for interactive controls lacking visible text labels.
- Maintain strong contrast, readable spacing, and clear visual hierarchy.
- Keep visual design aligned with a clean research-project and hackathon style.
